So the condition is:

if (visited) then:

   if (color(node) ! = c):

       then set mujun. and in any case return 0. Thus, the Fortran code needs to check if color(node) is not equal to -1, and not equal to c.

Wait actually, color(node) is >=0 (because when set, it's 0 or 1). So in fortran code, the check is:

if ( color(node) > =0 .AND. color(node)/= c )

then set mujun to true. But in any case, the function returns 0 (since it was already visited).
